prompt:
You are a requirements rewriter.
Rewrite each requirement into clean natural language suitable for UML state diagram generation.

Return ONLY valid JSON with this schema:
{
  "rewritten_requirements": [
    {
      "source_requirement": "string",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall ..."
    }
  ]
}

Rules:
1. Keep exactly the same number of requirements and same order.
2. Do not add new meaning.
3. Each rewritten requirement must start with "The system shall".
4. Keep them concise and implementation-neutral.

Input JSON:
{
  "functional_requirements": [
    {
      "requirement": "Maintain the date at which specific parts of a car are installed",
      "evidence_quote": "This application maintains the date at which the specific part of a car is installed"
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Notify expiry dates of car parts to both driver and authorized service centre",
      "evidence_quote": "notifies the expiry date of the parts of the car for both the driver and authorized service centre"
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Enable car owners and service centres to separately login and enter their cars' information",
      "evidence_quote": "This application enables car owners and service centres to separately login and enter their cars information"
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Allow service centre employee to enter estimated expiry dates of parts of the car after issuing the car",
      "evidence_quote": "the service centre employee enters the estimated expiry dates of parts of the car in this app"
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Notify car owners and service centres when expiry date for parts of the car is reached",
      "evidence_quote": "This application notifies the car owners and service centres when the expiry date for parts of the car is reached"
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Enable service centre employee to contact owner about service request after notification",
      "evidence_quote": "Then the service centre employee contacts the owner of a car about service, once the owner accepts service request"
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Allow owner to select damaged parts to be serviced through app",
      "evidence_quote": "once the owner selects the damaged parts to be serviced, the employee services the owner selected parts"
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Enable service centre employee to update information about changed parts in app",
      "evidence_quote": "the employee updates the information about changed parts in the app so that the car can be service again on the expiry date of changed parts"
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Allow online payment for services through app",
      "evidence_quote": "This application also enables the online payment for the services (Figures 14.1–14.8)"
    }
  ]
}

